    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Helping the Children</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from David Fox disagrees with May 21 letter objecting to granting paid leave to people who have children</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A May 21 letter objects to the granting of paid leave to people who have children, arguing that they should bear the cost of their choice.  It should be obvious that the beneficiaries of such assistance are the children -- a rather broad-based group you could call ''people who have parents.'' Having children may be a choice, but being a child is not.</p>
        <p>DAVID FOX  La Jolla, Calif., May 21, 2000</p>
      </block>
